article.description: Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 70, Sam Houston St. 68
article.headline: Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 70, Sam Houston St. 68
article.linkText: Texas A&amp,M-Corpus Christi 70, Sam Houston St. 68
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Garland Judkins had a career-high 17 points and Texas A&M-Corpus Christi held on to beat Sam Houston State 70-68 on Saturday night. Hollis Hill scored all seven of his points down the stretch for the Islanders (7-12, 2/3 Southland). His layup tied the game at 65, and two more baskets and a free throw closed it out. Demond Watt scored 12 points and Justin Reynolds scored 10, and each had seven rebounds for Texas A&M-Corpus Christi. Gilberto Clavell had a game-high 30 points and eight rebounds for Sam Houston State (9-9, 2-3). He scored the final three points for the Bearkats, but the closest they got was 69-68 with 5.4 seconds left. Hill made 1 of 2 free throws and a final Sam Houston State shot missed. Marcus Williams had 13 points for the Bearkats. Neither team led by more than six points in the game, which featured 10 ties.
